the tobacco companies have waged a major public relations offensive 
throughout the 4month trial 
the jury deliberated last week for four days beginning tuesday 
it took the weekend off and will return to the case monday 
lorillard inc liggett group inc and philip morris inc are 
accused of misleading the public about the dangers of cigarette 
smoking through advertising public relations and inadequate 
research 
antismoking advocates have hailed the trial as a gold mine of 
bad publicity for the 22 billion industry because of dozens of 
confidential company documents presented as evidence 
