and the plant was expected to begin pumping again on a limited 
basis on sunday 
the only injuries blamed on the quake felt in central and 
southern areas of the state were in whittier east of los angeles 
where a tree fell about the time of the temblor a woman and two 
men were treated for injuries said fire capt harold fullbright 
the quake also tumbled rocks onto interstate 5 close to the 
quakes center but traffic was not blocked the quake was also 
strong enough to knock goods off shelves at a wheeler ridge truck 
stop 
the temblor at 406 pm friday measured 52 on the richter 
scale it was centered on the garlock fault 11 miles 
northnortheast of gorman in the tehachapis northwest of los 
angeles according to seismologists at the california institute of 
technology in pasadena 
it was followed by a series of aftershocks the largest 
measuring 40 
the 200 milelong garlock fault is the secondlargest fault in 
california the largest is the 600 milelong san andreas fault 
the california aqueduct runs 440 miles from tracy near the 
sacramento river delta taking water that has flowed to the delta 
from rivers in northern california south to perris in riverside 
county it provides half of southern californias water 
</TEXT>
