<TEXT>
cavalrymen and foot soldiers in scarlet tunics and 
bearskin hats paraded in the center of london saturday to honor 
queen elizabeth ii with the trooping the color on her official 
birthday 
the queen who is 62 celebrated her real birthday on april 21 
but the official birthday ceremonies are held on the second 
saturday of june when the weather normally is better the sky was 
overcast and there was a damp chill in the air saturday 
this year for the first time since 1973 the 1588 men of all 
five regiments of the brigade of guards joined the parade because 
all are currently based in london 
the guards grenadier coldstream scots irish and welsh 
regiments are often scattered seeing service in such places as 
northern ireland and the falkland islands 
four generations of the royal family joined the ceremony this 
year riding in coaches or on horseback to the horse guards parade 
an open square in whitehall where the queen inspected the irish 
guards while massed bands played 
each year one regiment performs the honors marching in 
intricate patterns and carrying the color or regimental 
standard 
elizabeth wearing a blue coat and widebrimmed hat arrived in 
a horsedrawn phaeton and took the salute standing on a dais it 
was the second year she had used the carriage since retiring her 
horse burmese which she used to ride sidesaddle for the occasion 
wearing a scarlet uniform 
the queens 5yearold grandson prince william was with his 
mother the princess diana and his greatgrandmother queen mother 
elizabeth in her carriage 
riding horseback was the heir to the throne prince charles in 
his uniform as colonel of the welsh guards along with the queens 
husband prince philip a colonel of the grenadier guards 
on her return to buckingham palace the queen appeared on a 
balcony to wave to her subjects and thousands of tourists 
saturdays pageantry was based on the ceremony used for guard 
mounting in the 18th century and was first performed on the 
sovereigns birthday for king george iii but during the 18th and 
19th centuries the trooping was seldom attended by the monarch 
in 1895 the color was trooped in the quadrangle at windsor 
castle west of london and queen victoria took the salute from a 
carriage from that year on a senior royal person has always been 
in attendance 
