tipplers with a thirst for treasure got a chance 
saturday to bid at an auction of bottles of scotch and champagne 
recovered from a great lakes shipwreck 75 years ago 
susie shaw bought her dad some scotch whisky for a fathers day 
present three bottles that had been slowly vintaging in the cool 
waters of lake huron since the ss regina went down on nov 9 
1913 
it tastes very good said ms shaw of chicago who paid 180 
for the bottles of whyte amp mackay scotch whiskey and sampled some 
of the lakebed booze at a preauction tasting session its a 
novelty my father is a scotch drinker 
so far about 300 bottles of french champagne and scotch whisky 
have been salvaged from the regina one of 19 ships that went down 
in the great november storm 
several thousand more bottles still rest under 80 feet of water 
roughly 3 miles offshore from port sanilac about 80 miles 
northeast of detroit said commercial diver wayne brusate 
brusate accidentally discovered the wreck in july 1986 while 
searching for a tugboat that sank in the late 1960s 
i was surprised to find the cases of liquor said brusate 
of marysville mich most freighters on the great lakes carried 
