<TEXT>
federal scientists are secretly growing coca as 
part of an effort to learn how to eradicate the plant from which 
cocaine is derived according to a published report 
the new york times reported in sundays editions that the 
project has been kept secret because federal officials fear drug 
dealers or others might threaten the research program or its 
personnel 
researchers are looking for a reliable chemical or biological 
means to destroy coca in south american fields the source of most 
of the cocaine now reaching the united states 
the best prospect is a herbicide called tebuthurion 
manufactured under the trade name spike by eli lilly amp co 
environmentalists have expressed concern that the herbicide could 
be hazardous to the environment where coca is grown 
the cocagrowing project began about two years ago according to 
the times which ran photos of plants in a greenhouse near 
washington a reporter viewed experiments including the processing 
of coca into cocaine 
the newspaper agreed not to publish the identity of the 
researcher who granted access the site of the research complex or 
the federal agencies involved 
the project included several hundred coca bushes that were 
raised from seeds flown in from south america in diplomatic 
pouches the researcher told the times four varieties of the 
plants are being grown and researchers have found that herbicides 
that kill one variety may not work against others 
coca is very tough stuff the researcher said pointing out 
that a herbicidetreated stalk with brown and withered leaves was 
growing back 
