a french investigating magistrate has issued an 
international arrest warrant for alois brunner one of the last 
major nazi war criminals still at large he is believed to be 
living in syria 
brunner 76 adolf eichmanns righthand man was commander of 
the drancy transit camp from which thousands of french jews and 
resistance members were deported to concentration camps or 
extermination centers 
the arrest warrant was issued friday by judge claude grellier 
and follows a complaint filed dec 4 1987 accusing brunner of 
crimes against humanity specifically the kidnapping and murder of 
minors 
french lawyer and nazi hunter serge klarsfeld has entered the 
case as a civil party representing an organization called the sons 
and daughters of the jewish deportees of france 
klarsfeld along with his wife beate led the successful battle 
to have klaus barbie known as the butcher of lyon brought to 
france from bolivia in 1983 barbie was convicted of crimes against 
humanity last july and sentenced to life in prison france no 
longer has a death penalty 
brunner was tried and convicted in absentia in 1954 for war 
crimes and sentenced to death that sentence is no longer valid 
because the 20year statute of limitations has expired however 
there is no statute of limitations for crimes against humanity 
the charges against brunner involve the arrest of about 200 
children which the sons and daughters group says was carried out 
july 20 1944 and their deportation to the gas chambers at 
auschwitz in naziheld poland 
the klarsfelds in 1982 said they had found brunner in syria 
austria poland and west germany have previously asked for his 
extradition but the syrian government has never acted 
